			<node ID="ID_1307164666" TEXT="Future Value = Present Value x (1 + Discount Rate) Time Value of Money Examples. Now let&#8217;s look at time value of money examples. If you invest $100 (the present value) for 1 year at a 5% interest rate (the discount rate) then at the end of the year you would have $105 (the future value). So according to this example $100 today is worth " />
